    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of May 11 article in Circuits column on need to back up computer files</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The State of the Art column in Circuits on Thursday, about the need to back up computer files, invoked a 1777 aphorism from Samuel Johnson incorrectly. He said, ''Depend upon it, Sir, when a man knows he is to be hanged in a fortnight, it concentrates his mind wonderfully'' (not, ''Nothing focuses the mind as sharply as the news that one will be executed in a few days'').</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
